in Lebanon.

13:36.708 --> 13:37.917
I don't know, Tom.

13:37.999 --> 13:39.541
How you gonna keep 'em down
on the farm

13:39.625 --> 13:41.708
when they've seen the lobby
of every hotel in town?

13:41.792 --> 13:43.208
You make an example.

13:51.541 --> 13:54.999
(SIGHS) Well...
it's warm enough now.

13:55.083 --> 13:58.416
Yeah, I'll go into the village.
Get some firewood delivered.

13:59.333 --> 14:00.583
Enough to last me.

14:01.833 --> 14:04.583
-Got any heating here?
-Not much.

14:06.500 --> 14:08.792
What'll you do in the winter?

14:08.875 --> 14:10.875
Winter's not gonna touch me,
man.

14:15.875 --> 14:17.083
(SNIFFS)

14:25.999 --> 14:27.083
Rudy's gone.

14:28.750 --> 14:29.875
What do you mean?

14:31.458 --> 14:32.541
He's dead.

14:33.917 --> 14:35.208
His people did him.

14:36.541 --> 14:37.999
The way they do, you know.

14:39.625 --> 14:40.667
How?

14:42.249 --> 14:43.291
In his car.

14:44.500 --> 14:47.416
Up on 49th, at the river.

14:48.375 --> 14:49.500
Shot in the head.

14:51.416 --> 14:53.333
Why'd they do him like that?

14:57.416 --> 14:58.917
So, now it's just Tommy.

14:59.625 --> 15:00.958
The new capo.

15:02.999 --> 15:04.625
Tommy ain't right in the head.

15:06.041 --> 15:07.833
You know, he...

15:07.917 --> 15:11.291
thinks something and...
his trigger finger reacts.

15:11.375 --> 15:12.583
You think he did Rudy?

15:12.667 --> 15:13.999
I don't know.

15:14.083 --> 15:17.458
But I've seen him do people,
so I know he will.

15:19.249 --> 15:21.667
Whatever Rudy had
is now his.

15:22.667 --> 15:24.999
(MIKE COUGHS)

15:28.041 --> 15:32.333
Look, you, uh... You want me
to get you some, uh...

15:34.124 --> 15:36.249
medicine or somethin'?
I don't know. (EXHALES)

15:36.333 --> 15:37.333
No.

15:38.083 --> 15:39.166
I'm good.

15:42.999 --> 15:44.958
Wish they had a phone
in here.

15:45.041 --> 15:46.708
We could at least talk.

15:46.792 --> 15:49.208
I can call you from town...
time to time.

15:51.333 --> 15:53.458
(SIGHS)

15:54.917 --> 15:57.083
I will come back up here
next month.

15:57.166 --> 15:58.333
Sure thing.

16:00.500 --> 16:01.541
We had fun, man.

16:02.041 --> 16:03.500
(LAUGHS)

16:04.875 --> 16:05.999
Yeah, we did.

16:06.667 --> 16:07.750
(COUGHS)

16:08.958 --> 16:10.041
Yeah.

16:12.750 --> 16:14.208
My father used to say...

16:15.458 --> 16:17.416
"Never let anything
walk by you."

16:18.750 --> 16:20.917
I took his advice.

16:20.999 --> 16:23.667
I don't believe I left
one stone unturned.

16:23.750 --> 16:26.124
(CHUCKLES)

16:26.208 --> 16:27.541
(MIKE SIGHS)

16:29.708 --> 16:31.041
(CUP CLINKS)

16:32.375 --> 16:33.750
You remember Honey?

16:34.750 --> 16:35.875
Of course.

16:36.999 --> 16:38.375
Honey was somethin'.

16:39.333 --> 16:40.500
All of 'em.

16:41.667 --> 16:43.124
The whole parade, man.

16:44.583 --> 16:45.708
They were rich.

16:49.583 --> 16:51.083
I ain't got no regrets.

16:54.041 --> 16:55.458
I drink from the cup.

17:06.583 --> 17:07.625
Mike...

17:09.583 --> 17:10.583
What?

17:11.792 --> 17:12.958
(SIGHS)

17:13.917 --> 17:14.917
Shit.

17:16.625 --> 17:18.083
This is hard for me.

17:20.999 --> 17:22.416
-I--
-Shh.

17:23.708 --> 17:25.333
Let's enjoy this fire.

17:50.458 --> 17:51.833
(KEYS JINGLE)

17:51.917 --> 17:54.249
AMY GOLDMAN: Michael's
saying goodbye to some friends

17:54.333 --> 17:55.833
before he leaves for school.

17:58.166 --> 17:59.667
That's great.

17:59.750 --> 18:00.917
(KEYS JINGLE)

18:03.500 --> 18:04.958
It's quiet in this house.

18:06.750 --> 18:08.333
It is. (CLEARS THROAT)

18:09.833 --> 18:11.291
This isn't fair to me.

18:14.792 --> 18:15.833
I understand.

18:18.041 --> 18:19.333
I understand.

18:23.041 --> 18:24.625
I'm sorry I hurt you...

18:29.667 --> 18:33.249
but I don't regret
the time we had together...

18:33.333 --> 18:34.458
(SNIFFS)

18:35.541 --> 18:37.166
...or the family that we made.

18:42.833 --> 18:43.875
I'll, uh...

18:46.708 --> 18:49.208
